Docs.typeparam: The contract type of the objects in the list.
Docs.summary: Represents a generic list of types that are defined by a contract and are used to pass collections of that contract type between a host and an add-in.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.AddIn.Pipeline.CollectionAdapters> class uses an <xref:System.AddIn.Contract.IListContract%601> interface to pass collections, in both directions, between the host and the add-in. It is recommended that you use the <xref:System.AddIn.Pipeline.CollectionAdapters> class instead of using this class directly in your code. For an example, see [Walkthrough: Passing Collections Between Hosts and Add-Ins](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/b532c604-548e-4fab-b11c-377257dd0ee5).
This class can be used to pass objects by reference between application domains because the objects are not serialized.
